{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it was-- they were, they were making butter, and you know, like-- like in a wholesale place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So later he switched, and he did photography.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so part-- the photography, he used to do in the house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was very much involved in raising the children and participating with us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the photography, he was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was always had two people at home-- my grandmother, and-- I remember, summer we used to go away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never went to a camp, all my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Never was away a day from my parents, alone, till age 13.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But every summer-- my mother, as I mentioned, had the-- she was one of seven.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But unfortunately, two died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The older son and the youngest daughter died.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What were their names?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The oldest, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But because-- maybe because he didn't live, so they didn't-- but the youngest, I do know-- [?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Kyla. ?] I have a photograph of her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, I never saw the photograph before the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was lucky.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I got it after the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I'll tell you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before I was born yet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, but the others, I had one uncle which at age 18 emigrated from Poland to England, to London, England.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There he met and married a woman who came with a large family from Russia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Brest-Litsk, ?] I think it was called.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they got married, and they had six children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Also was very religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they left--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What was the name?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I wrote down the names.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know it was Gerald, Bob, [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Esme-- ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, my uncle?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Moishe Pinchas Zebrak.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Zebrak.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was my grandmother's.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Z-E-B-R-A-K.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They lived in England.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
